Change can be frightening, and it's rarely easy to leave situations that you're comfortable and familiar with, even when you know it's for the best. I have cherished so many good things during my time working with Tootsies over the years. I have formed incredible friendships and have been presented with numerous opportunities to collaborate and grow with other aspiring artists. I will forever be grateful for these experiences and for meeting all of you who have supported me and all the band members I’ve worked with.
🎵 
That being said, my time at Tootsies, Kid Rocks, and Honkytonk Central has come to an end. Our visions for what was best for me, my band, and the Nashville music community were no longer aligned, and it was time to say goodbye. If you search "Honkytonk School Nashville Tootsies" on Google, you'll find all the information to understand why this change was necessary.
😈
The amount of love shown to my entire crew has been beyond words, and I'm deeply grateful for all the kindness everyone has shown me. Thanks to that kindness, we will be back at work full-time very soon, and our new schedules will be posted on our stories. Please keep an eye out for them!
👀
Once again, thank you all for your unwavering support. I love each and every one of you.
😊
Josh
#nashville #countrymusic #news #change
